        ],
        [
          "You were a straight A student, who excelled your way right into the Tremere chantry. At first a ghoul, you were being groomed for the Embrace and looked forward to all the secrets you'd eventually learn. However, your regent somehow decided that an artifact held by the Nosferatu was worth more than you, and so you were traded away (after a mind wipe to make you forget the really important secrets). You were tortured for awhile, your mind picked apart as the Nosferatu attempted to recover whatever scraps they could of what you'd been made to forget. You didn't blame them, not really - you *really* blamed the Tremere, resenting them for treating you like a commodity. You parlayed your bitterness into a one-Kindred war against them, becoming the best spymaster you could. Your hunger for secrets has led you to someone named Samuel Price, who has brought you to the infernal. You haven't signed on the dotted line, not yet, but you're open to the idea. During the game, you can call upon your infernal pact for a minor effect - at the cost of your soul (and your unlife, if anyone learns what you've done)."
